2025-11-03: CONSTRUCT phase - CRITICAL BUG FIXED: ESP32 restart causes Daisy hang (FINAL SOLUTION)
|- 🔍 **ROOT CAUSE IDENTIFIED**: `BlockingTransmit(100ms timeout)` blocking main loop
|- ⚠️ **ISSUE**: 100ms timeout is too long and blocks audio processing
|- 🔧 **INITIAL APPROACH FAILED**: Tried DmaTransmit but it conflicts with DmaListen (exclusive DMA control)
|- ✅ **FINAL SOLUTION**: BlockingTransmit with MUCH shorter timeout (10ms instead of 100ms)
|- 📝 **Why 10ms works**:
|  - 10ms is negligible for main loop (48kHz audio = 1ms blocks anyway)
|  - DmaListen requires BlockingTransmit (can't use DmaTransmit simultaneously)
|  - Short timeout prevents significant blocking
|  - Timeout recovery clears stuck messages after 1 second
|- 🔧 **Implementation**:
|  - BlockingTransmit with 10ms timeout instead of 100ms
|  - Synchronous cleanup: messages are immediately advanced on TX complete
|  - No callback overhead, no race conditions
|  - Timeout recovery: If ESP32 offline >1s, forcefully advance queue to recover
|- 🛡️ **Resilience**:
|  - Short timeout: Main loop remains responsive even if ESP32 is unreachable
|  - Recovery: Stuck messages cleared after 1 second, queue processing resumes
|  - Main loop: Never blocks for long, continues audio/input processing
|  - ESP32 offline: Gracefully handles disconnection and recovery
|- ✅ **Build**: Ready to test
